headline: 'Mag 7' turned 'Mid 7': Is 2025 the end of tech dominance?
summary: The tech sector (XLK), specifically the "Magnificent Seven," made up of Nvidia (NVDA), Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL), Tesla (TSLA), Microsoft (MSFT), Amazon (AMZN), Meta (META), and Apple (AAPL), was a significant driver of market gains in 2023 and 2024. However, 2025 has been a different story so far. Yahoo Finance Markets Reporter Josh Schafer and Wall Street Alliance Group partner Aadil Zaman sit down with Brad Smith on Catalysts to take a look at how the Magnificent Seven has underperformed the wider market in 2025. headline: German utility RWE and tech giant Amazon announce partnership
summary: PARIS (Reuters) -German utility RWE and tech giant Amazon announced a strategic framework agreement on Thursday, where the utility will provide clean power delivery and in exchange receive cloud services.  The cloud services cover artificial intelligence and data analytics in exchange for electricity supplied from RWE's wind and solar facilities, some of which are already in operation and some are under construction.  RWE is a major utility in Europe with a large portfolio of renewable energy both in operation and in development which it can then sell to Amazon or other data centre hyperscalers to help companies reach green energy targets.
